Firstly, the fundamentals of zoonotic disease must be addressed and resolved. In the case of China, where three of the last five global pandemics originated, practices such as wildlife "farming", "wet markets" and consumption must be legislated out of existence.

These practices, which began within only the last 50 years when China was having difficulty feeding its population, are responsible for untolled sickness, mass mortality and huge productivity and financial losses.

In less than four months, coronavirus has resulted in hundreds of thousands of infections, thousands of deaths, quarantines of tens of millions of people, the shuttering of much of large swathes of critical production capacity and the loss of trillions of dollars in world markets.

All the result of one human coming into contact with one animal infected with a virus from another species due solely to unnatural exposure that was the result of ill-advised wildlife farming, transport, confinement, marketing, slaughter and consumption.

These are the origins of global pandemics that must be remedied. The old adage, "an ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure" has never been more true.

Trillions of dollars have already been lost. Entire regions and countries have been shutdown. Industry has been idled. Healthcare costs are incalculable. Billions of dollars have been allocated to address this pandemic.

A worldwide protocol to which every country abides is long overdue.

Remember, owing to insufficient financial incentive, treatments and vaccines for past zoonotic diseases, such as SARS and MERS still do not exist! This is a blueprint that all but guarantees the continuation of global pandemics.
